This paper deals with Named Entity Recognition and Relation Extraction for Chinese literature text, which falls under the domain of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which could be relevant to researchers in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
